==Awards==
===Liverpool Players awards===
The Players' Awards were held on 19 May at the [[Echo Arena Liverpool|Echo Arena]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.liverpoolfc.com/2015-players-awards/home|title=2015 Players Awards|date=18 May 2015|work=Official Site Liverpool FC|accessdate=19 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425042229/http://www.liverpoolfc.com/2015-players-awards/home|archive-date=25 April 2016|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url= http://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/latest-news/185522-phil-wins-four-prizes-at-players-awards|title=Phil wins four prizes at Players' Awards|date=19 May 2015|work=Official Site Liverpool FC|accessdate=19 May 2015}}</ref>	
	
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool Player's Player of the Year Award]]: [[Philippe Coutinho]]
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool Supporter's Player of the Year Award]]: [[Philippe Coutinho]]
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool Supporter's Young Player of the Year Award]]: [[Raheem Sterling]]
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Goal of the Season Award]]: [[Philippe Coutinho]] for his long range strike v Southampton, February 22.
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Performance of the Year]]: [[Philippe Coutinho]] v Manchester City, March 1
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Outstanding Achievement Award]]: [[Steven Gerrard]]
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Academy Players' Player of the Year]]: [[João Carlos Teixeira]] 
*[[Liverpool F.C.|Lifetime Achievement Award]]: [[Ron Yeats]] and [[Ian St John]]

